                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/15235.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Special Agent <persName type="from">Silliman</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vera Cruz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-06-15T19:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 15, 1915—7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s June 15, noon, presented personally to General Carranza, who thanks
                    Department for its good offices, replying that General Gonzalez has the
                    necessary instructions to determine any proposition made by the forces at
                    present occupying the city. My impression is that the government occupying the
                    city is considered to have little importance and any agreement entered into
                    would be respected by neither Villa nor Zapata. I am informed that General
                    Gonzalez will be perfectly fair and that foreigners and their interests will not
                    be molested. The authorities should at the proper time confer with him regarding
                    a peaceful entry.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Silliman.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
